comments.body:
Apparently Valkyrie can register a finalizer to close the IO stream if it's garbage collected.

Edit: I can't get this to reliably work in a testable way in Ruby 2.x

So I think Valkyrie needs to:

* Provide access to #close 
* Not open a file descriptor until you're trying to read the content of a file.

figgy.title: [Figgy/production] TypeError: no implicit conversion of nil into Array

comments.body:
Honeybadger reports that the error is happening in line:

```
return nil unless earliest_date | latest_date
```

This is probably because one of the dates is `nil` instead of an array. 

The `|` works fine when both values are arrays:

```
earliest = [1]
latest = [2]
earliest | latest
=> [1, 2]
```

but blows up with one of the values is `nil`

```
earliest = [1]
latest = nil
earliest | latest

Traceback (most recent call last):
        5: from /Users/correah/.rubies/ruby-2.6.6/bin/irb:23:in `<main>'
        4: from /Users/correah/.rubies/ruby-2.6.6/bin/irb:23:in `load'
        3: from /Users/correah/.rubies/ruby-2.6.6/lib/ruby/gems/2.6.0/gems/irb-1.0.0/exe/irb:11:in `<top (required)>'
        2: from (irb):29
        1: from (irb):29:in `|'
TypeError (no implicit conversion of nil into Array)
```
